Mix flour, parsley flakes, thyme, salt, ginger, nutmeg and pepper in large plastic food storage bag. Add pork. Shake to coat. Heat CRISCO(R) Oil in Dutch oven. Add pork and any remaining flour mixture. Brown over medium-high heat. Stir in remaining ingredients except zucchini. Heat to boiling. Cover. Reduce heat. Simmer, stirring occasionally, 1-1/2 to 2 hours. Add zucchini; re-cover. Simmer 30 minutes longer, or until pork is tender. Remove and discard bay leaf.